    <div class="space-y-6">
      <section id="chap1" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 1</span> Preamble and Acceptance
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>1.1</strong> Welcome to Qomicex Launcher ("the Software" or "QML"). The Software is an open-source Minecraft game launcher developed and maintained by the Qomicex development team ("we", "us", or "the Developer").</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>1.2</strong> Please read this User Agreement ("this Agreement") carefully. By using, downloading, installing, or running the Software in any way, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to be bound by this Agreement. If you do not agree to any term of this Agreement, please cease using the Software immediately.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>1.3</strong> The Software is released under the <strong>GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3)</strong>. Nothing in this Agreement shall be construed as limiting your rights under the GPLv3.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap2" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 2</span> Definitions
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3">Unless otherwise expressly defined in this Agreement, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"Software" or "QML"</strong>: Qomicex Launcher, including its executable files, source code, documentation, and all features and services provided through the Software.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"Service"</strong>: All functionality provided by the Software to you, including but not limited to game instance management, resource downloads, account management, and multiplayer features.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"User" or "you"</strong>: Any individual or legal entity using the Software.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"User Content"</strong>: Any data stored, managed, or processed by you through the Software, including but not limited to game saves, resource packs, mods, screenshots, and settings preferences.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"Third-Party Service"</strong>: Services or APIs integrated into or referenced by the Software that are operated by third parties, including but not limited to Modrinth, CurseForge, FTB, and Microsoft authentication services.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>"Minecraft"</strong>: The sandbox game developed by Mojang Studios (now a subsidiary of Microsoft).</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="chap3" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 3</span> Service Description
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>3.1 Service Overview</strong>. The Software is a cross-platform Minecraft game launcher designed to provide users with a convenient game management experience. The current version is <strong>v0.1.x</strong>, which is in the testing stage.</p>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong>3.2 Core Features</strong>. The main features of the Software include but are not limited to:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Game Instance Management</strong>: Create, configure, and manage multiple independent Minecraft game instances with version isolation.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Download Center</strong>: Download Minecraft game versions, loaders (Forge, Fabric, NeoForge, Quilt, etc.), and Java runtimes from multiple sources.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Resource Center</strong>: Browse, search, and download mods, resource packs, and modpacks from platforms such as Modrinth and CurseForge.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Account Management</strong>: Support for Microsoft accounts (OAuth), Yggdrasil authentication servers (third-party login), Unified Pass, and offline mode.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Multiplayer Module</strong>: LAN and mesh networking features based on EasyTier technology.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Settings and Updates</strong>: Application settings management and automatic update checking and installation.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>3.3 Service Status</strong>. The Software is currently in beta and may contain errors or defects. We will make commercially reasonable efforts to improve the service quality but make no guarantees regarding continuous availability, error-free operation, or suitability.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>3.4 Supported Platforms</strong>. The Software supports the following operating systems: Windows (x64 / ARM64), macOS (x64 / ARM64), Linux (x64 / ARM64 / LoongArch64 / RISC-V 64). The user experience may vary across different platforms.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap4" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 4</span> User Accounts
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong>4.1 Account Types</strong>. The Software supports the following account types:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Microsoft Account</strong>: Authenticated via the Microsoft OAuth 2.0 protocol. This process is handled entirely by Microsoft's platform; the Software only receives the authorized access token.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Yggdrasil (Third-Party Login)</strong>: Allows users to connect to custom AuthlibInjector-compatible authentication servers.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Unified Pass</strong>: A third-party Yggdrasil authentication service (e.g. <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">login.mc-user.com</code>), with registration and authentication provided by community server operators.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Offline Mode</strong>: No online authentication required; only a username is needed.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>4.2 Account Information Security</strong>. Your account credentials (including access tokens) are stored in an encrypted file on your local machine. We will not upload your credentials to any unnecessary third-party server. The encryption is tied to your machine's hardware identifier; changing your device may render stored credentials inaccessible.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>4.3 User Responsibility</strong>. You are responsible for safeguarding your account credentials. We shall not be held liable for any loss or legal liability resulting from your disclosure of credentials or account sharing.</p>

        <div class="admonition danger">
          <strong>Important:</strong> The Software does not collect or store your Microsoft account password in any form. The Microsoft OAuth process is carried out entirely on Microsoft's platform.
        </div>
      </section>

      <section id="chap5" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 5</span> Code of Conduct
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>5.1 Lawful Use</strong>. You agree to use the Software only for lawful purposes and to comply with all applicable laws and regulations. You must not use the Software for any illegal activities.</p>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong>5.2 Prohibited Actions</strong>. When using the Software, you shall not:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify">Reverse engineer, decompile, or disassemble the Software, except as expressly permitted by applicable law or the GPLv3 license;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">Use the Software for any activity that infringes upon third-party intellectual property rights;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">Distribute malware, viruses, or any destructive code through the Software;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">Interfere with or disrupt the normal operation of the Software in any manner;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">Violate the Minecraft End User License Agreement (Minecraft EULA) published by Mojang Studios;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">Use the Software for any commercial purpose without prior written permission from us.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>5.3 Open Source Compliance</strong>. The Software is released under the GPLv3 license. When exercising the rights granted by the GPLv3, you must comply with all terms and conditions of that license. If any provision of this Agreement conflicts with the GPLv3, the GPLv3 shall prevail.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap6" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 6</span> Third-Party Services
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>6.1 Overview</strong>. The Software integrates multiple third-party services and APIs to provide you with a rich set of features. These third-party services are independently maintained by their respective operators.</p>
        <p class="mb-3"><strong>6.2 List of Third-Party Services</strong>. The third-party services currently used by the Software include:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Modrinth API</strong> (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">https://api.modrinth.com/v2/</code>): Used to search for and retrieve mod, resource pack, and modpack information.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>CurseForge API</strong> (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">https://api.curseforge.com</code>): Used to search for and retrieve resource information from the CurseForge platform.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>FTB API</strong> (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">https://api.feed-the-beast.com</code>): Used to retrieve FTB modpack information.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Microsoft Authentication Service</strong>: Used for the Microsoft account OAuth login flow.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>mclo.gs</strong> (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">https://api.mclo.gs/1/log</code>): Used for user-initiated crash log sharing.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>mcmod.cn</strong>: Used to retrieve Chinese data indices for mods.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>GitHub API</strong> (<code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">https://api.github.com</code>): Used to check for application updates.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>BMCLAPI / MCIM Mirrors</strong>: Used to accelerate downloads of Minecraft game files and related resources.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>6.3 Third-Party Service Disclaimer</strong>. We are not responsible for the content, availability, accuracy, or legality of any third-party service. When using third-party services, you should comply with their respective terms and policies. Any issues or disputes arising from third-party services shall be resolved between you and the applicable third-party operator.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>6.4 API Usage Limits</strong>. Third-party APIs may have rate limits or other usage restrictions. We shall not be held liable for any functional anomalies caused by third-party API limitations.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap7" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 7</span> Intellectual Property
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>7.1 Intellectual Property of the Software</strong>. The source code, documentation, and related materials of Qomicex Launcher are protected by copyright law and international copyright treaties. The Software is released under the <strong>GNU General Public License v3.0 (GPLv3)</strong>. You have the right to use, copy, modify, and distribute the Software in accordance with the terms of the GPLv3.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>7.2 User Content</strong>. The intellectual property rights of user content you create, store, or manage through the Software (including but not limited to game saves, screenshots, and mod configurations) belong to you or the respective rights holders. You grant us a non-exclusive, royalty-free license to use such content to the extent necessary to provide the Software's services.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>7.3 Minecraft Intellectual Property</strong>. The intellectual property rights of the Minecraft game and its related brands, logos, and assets belong to Mojang Studios and/or Microsoft Corporation. The Software is not affiliated with, sponsored by, or authorized by Mojang Studios or Microsoft Corporation.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>7.4 Third-Party Resources</strong>. The intellectual property rights of mods, resource packs, modpacks, and other resources you download or access through the Software belong to their respective creators or rights holders. You should comply with the applicable license terms when using these resources.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap8" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 8</span> Privacy Notice
        </h2>

        <div class="admonition note">
          <strong>Core Principle: The Software does not contain any telemetry, analytics, or automatic data collection features.</strong> We respect your privacy.
        </div>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>8.1 Locally Stored Data</strong>. The Software stores the following data on your local machine:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Application Settings</strong>: Stored in <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&#123;data directory&#125;/QML/settings.json</code>, including interface preferences, download settings, and Java paths.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Account Credentials</strong>: Stored in <code class="font-mono text-xs bg-muted text-primary px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded">&#123;data directory&#125;/data/accounts.dat</code>, encrypted and bound to your machine's hardware identifier.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Browser Local Storage (localStorage)</strong>: Including update channel preference, update deferral information, managed instance directory list, and view mode preference.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Java Runtime Information</strong>: Cache of scanned system Java installations.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Download Tasks</strong>: Cache of incomplete download task information.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify">All of the above data is <strong>stored entirely on your local device</strong> and is not automatically sent to any remote server.</p>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>8.2 Crash Log Upload</strong>. When you choose to use the crash analysis feature, the crash log content is sent to the <strong>mclo.gs</strong> third-party service to generate a shareable link. This is a <strong>user-initiated action</strong>, not an automatic upload. The Software will display the content to be uploaded before sending it.</p>

        <p class="mb-3"><strong>8.3 Network Requests</strong>. During normal use, the Software makes network requests to the following types of servers:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Minecraft Resource Servers</strong>: To download game files, libraries, and assets.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Third-Party API Services</strong> (Modrinth, CurseForge, FTB, etc.): To search and retrieve resource information.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Microsoft Authentication Service</strong>: To handle the account login flow.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>GitHub API</strong>: To check for application updates.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Mirror Servers</strong> (BMCLAPI, MCIM, etc.): To accelerate downloads.</li>
          <li class="text-justify"><strong>Custom Authentication Servers</strong>: To connect to Yggdrasil authentication servers based on your configuration.</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify">All requests above are triggered by your active actions and do not involve invisible data reporting.</p>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>8.4 Data Retention and Deletion</strong>. You can clear all local data by resetting application settings or manually deleting the data directory. After you cease using the Software, locally stored data will remain on your device until you actively delete it.</p>

        <p class="mb-3"><strong>8.5 Third-Party Privacy Policies</strong>. The third-party services integrated into the Software have their own independent privacy policies. We recommend reviewing the following privacy policies:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
          <li><a href="https://privacy.microsoft.com" target="_blank" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-85">Microsoft Privacy Statement</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://modrinth.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-85">Modrinth Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.overwolf.com/legal/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-85">CurseForge Privacy Policy</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://aternos.gmbh/en/mclogs/privacy" target="_blank" class="text-primary underline underline-offset-2 hover:opacity-85">mclo.gs Privacy Policy</a></li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section id="chap9" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 9</span> Disclaimer of Warranties
        </h2>

        <div class="admonition warning">
          <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> The Software is provided on an "as is" and "as available" basis, without any warranties of any kind, either express or implied.
        </div>

        <p class="mb-3">To the fullest extent permitted by law, we expressly disclaim all warranties of any kind, including but not limited to:</p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-3 space-y-1.5">
