          <li class="text-justify">That the operation of the Software will be uninterrupted, timely, secure, or error-free;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">The accuracy, reliability, or completeness of any information or content obtained through the Software;</li>
          <li class="text-justify">That defects in the Software will be corrected.</li>
        </ul>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>9.2 No Affiliation with Mojang/Microsoft</strong>. The Software is an independent third-party tool and is not affiliated with, sponsored by, endorsed by, or authorized by Mojang Studios, Microsoft Corporation, or their affiliates. Minecraft is a trademark of Mojang AB.</p>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>9.3 Mods and Third-Party Resources</strong>. Any mods, resource packs, modpacks, or other third-party resources that you download, install, or use through the Software are not provided or warranted by us. We assume no responsibility for the quality, safety, legality, or suitability of these resources.</p>

        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>9.4 Beta Version</strong>. The Software is currently in beta and may contain undiscovered defects or compatibility issues. You voluntarily assume all risks associated with using the beta version.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap10" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 10</span> Limitation of Liability
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>10.1</strong> To the fullest extent permitted by law, neither we nor our contributors, licensors, or affiliates shall be liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages arising out of or relating to the use of or inability to use the Software, including but not limited to data loss, business interruption, loss of profits, loss of goodwill, or software malfunction.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>10.2</strong> These limitations shall apply even if we have been advised of the possibility of such damages. Some jurisdictions do not allow the exclusion or limitation of certain warranties or liability, so the above limitations may not apply to you. In such cases, our liability shall be limited to the minimum extent permitted by applicable law.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>10.3</strong> Regardless of the legal theory (contract, tort, strict liability, or otherwise), our total cumulative liability shall not exceed any fees (if any) paid by you for using the Software in the six months preceding the claim.</p>
      </section>

      <section id="chap11" class="rounded-xl border border-border bg-card p-8">
        <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-foreground mb-5 pb-2.5 border-b border-border">
          <span class="text-primary mr-2">Chapter 11</span> Termination
        </h2>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>11.1 Voluntary Termination</strong>. You may stop using the Software and delete all copies at any time, without notice.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>11.2 Termination for Breach</strong>. If you violate any term of this Agreement, all rights granted to you shall automatically terminate without notice. Upon termination, you must immediately cease using the Software and delete all copies.</p>
        <p class="mb-3 text-justify"><strong>11.3 Effect of Termination</strong>. After termination, the following provisions shall remain in effect: Chapter 7 (Intellectual Property), Chapter 8 (Privacy Notice), Chapter 9 (Disclaimer of Warranties), Chapter 10 (Limitation of Liability), Chapter 12 (Governing Law and Dispute Resolution), and Chapter 13 (Changes to This Agreement).</p>
